## General Pebble Project Learnings
*Reference SOP wisdom: Consolidated guardrails from past friction points. See SOP_Guide.md for actionable format.*
*Reusable insights applicable to any Pebble smartwatch app*

### Build & Compilation
- **Math functions require explicit headers**: Use `#include <math.h>` for sin(), cos(), sqrt() functions
- **Standard library macros may not exist**: Avoid MAX/MIN macros; use conditional logic instead
- **All platforms must rebuild cleanly**: Test at least aplite (smallest), basalt (standard), and chalk (round) before considering complete
- **pebble build output is verbose**: Grep for "finished" or "error" to quickly validate build status
- **Clean before major refactors**: Run `pebble clean` to avoid cached object file issues with header changes

### Animations & Graphics
- **Use floats (0.0-1.0) for opacity, not 0-255**: Easier to reason about and standard in animation systems
- **Manual canvas updates require layer_mark_dirty()**: Property animations handle this; custom opacity logic doesn't
- **Breathing/pulsing feels less mechanical with sine waves**: Use `sin(elapsed * PI / period) * amplitude` for organic feel
- **Prefer subtle animations (2px amplitude, 3-5s period)**: Distracting animations harm user experience on glance-first design
- **Window transitions need animated=true**: Animated push/pop avoids jarring frame jumps (use `window_stack_push()` with `WindowFullscreen` and animated)
- **Test animations on small screens too**: aplite (144×168) reveals if effects are too aggressive; breathing should be barely perceptible at smallest sizes
- **TextLayers vs graphics_draw_text() context matters**: 
  - TextLayers: For dynamic text that changes frequently; layers persist across frames (memory cost ~80 bytes/layer)
  - graphics_draw_text() in canvas_update_proc: For static or infrequently-changing text within structured layouts (pixel-perfect geometry)
  - Both have valid use cases; don't assume one is universally superior
- **Canvas rendering order matters**: Draw backgrounds first, then content, then overlays (confetti/floating text on top)
- **graphics_fill_rect corner radius**: Rounded corners use `graphics_fill_rect(ctx, rect, radius, GCornersAll)` not separate function
- **Font selection impacts reliability**: FONT_KEY_GOTHIC_28_BOLD more reliable than FONT_KEY_LECO_28_LIGHT_NUMBERS; leco font optimized for simple digits only

### Platform Compatibility
- **Relative positioning beats hardcoded coordinates**: Use grect_inset(), layer_set_bounds() with percentages
- **Test on at least 3 different aspect ratios**: Rectangular (basalt 200×228), square-ish (aplite 144×168), and circular (chalk 260×260)
- **Font sizing differs across platforms**: Text that fits perfectly on basalt may wrap on aplite; leave padding
- **Circular displays hide edges**: Chalk/gabbro cut off beyond radius; design with safe area centered
- **All platforms must handle same memory constraints**: Avoid assuming basalt/emery have extra resources vs aplite
- **PBL_ROUND macro enables platform-specific rendering**: Use `#if defined(PBL_ROUND)` for conditional code paths between rectangular and circular displays
- **Round display rectangular layouts still work**: Grid layout fitted to circular bounds clips naturally; no special circular math required for basic layouts

### State Management
- **Initialize all state variables in window_load**: Don't rely on global init; some platforms may skip main()
- **Use s_ prefix convention for static globals**: Makes it clear what persists across function calls
- **Animation state needs cleanup in window_unload**: Call `animation_unschedule()` and reset context to prevent crashes
- **UTC epoch-based streak logic beats simple dates**: Using milliseconds since 1970 prevents timezone/DST cheating on streak counters
- **Persistent storage survives app crashes**: Use carefully; outdated data is worse than missing data

### PKJS Integration (Phone Side)
- **AppMessage works bidirectionally**: Watch can send AND receive; design for both flows
- **Message keys must match package.json exactly**: Auto-generated headers depend on dictionary keys matching precisely
- **Pondering Personas or similar flavor text boost engagement**: Low effort, high impact on app personality
- **Daily content (prompts, quotes) needs rotation algorithm**: Simple day-of-year modulo prevents repetition without server; users still see variety

### Testing Approaches
- **Screenshot every major UI change**: Visual diff catches issues code review often misses
- **Use pebble emu-button for interaction testing**: Can script button sequences for end-to-end flows (SELECT→DOWN→BACK)
- **Test sleep/wake cycles**: Some state bugs only appear after lock/unlock
- **Verify on emulator VNC if running headless**: Add `--vnc` flag to all emulator commands in CI/headless environments
- **Performance bottleneck: canvas redraws**: Animate via opacity float, not by redrawing complex graphics per frame

### Design Philosophy
- **Glance-first**: Information must be visible in <2 seconds before user scrolls/interacts
- **Black and white looks premium and saves battery**: Color adds minimal value but ~25% power cost
- **One action per button reduces cognitive load**: Each button should have ONE primary function
- **Motivational streaks are addictive ethically**: Streak design should encourage sustainable habits, not obsessive behavior
- **Breathing animations signal "zen mode"**: Sinusoidal motion implies calm/meditative; perfect for reflection/wellness apps

### UI Rendering & Typography
- **High-contrast text improves readability significantly**: White on dark backgrounds, black on light backgrounds (tested across all 4-color palette)
- **Bold fonts work better than light for small devices**: FONT_KEY_GOTHIC_28_BOLD more legible than FONT_KEY_LECO_28_LIGHT_NUMBERS on small screens
- **Rounded corners (6px) improve visual softness without performance cost**: Inexpensive to render, high visual impact
- **Persistent text buffers required for graphics_draw_text()**: Must use static/global buffers, not local variables; Pebble graphics API stores text pointer, not copy
- **Gutter spacing preserves visual hierarchy**: 4px gutters between quadrants sufficient to separate elements without wasting screen real estate
- **Selection indicators should use high-contrast colors**: White borders on colored backgrounds visible without additional effects
- **Header separation from content aids glance-first design**: 20px header with title clearly delineates navigation/branding from gameplay area

### Memory Optimization (Phase 1 Result)
- **Removing TextLayer allocations saves meaningful memory**: Eliminated 8 TextLayer objects (P1-P4 names + scores) = ~640 bytes saved per app load
- **Graphics API trades memory for code complexity**: Requires persistent text buffers and update callbacks, but simpler than TextLayer state management
- **Canvas-based rendering preferred for complex layouts**: Single canvas update_proc easier to coordinate than multiple-layer composition

### B&W Platform Support (Phase 4 Result)
- **B&W platforms (aplite, diorite, flint) initially showed blank/white screens**: Diorite (Pebble 2) and Flint (Pebble 2 Duo) have PBL_COLOR defined but don't handle color rendering properly, resulting in invisible colored backgrounds
- **Platform-specific B&W detection crucial**: Cannot rely on PBL_COLOR alone; must explicitly check device platform with `#if defined(PBL_PLATFORM_APLITE) || defined(PBL_PLATFORM_DIORITE) || defined(PBL_PLATFORM_FLINT)` macro
- **Player identification via names sufficient**: Initial numbered badges (1, 2, 3, 4) in top-right corner were redundant when player names "P1", "P2", "P3", "P4" already displayed; simpler design without badges
- **Text contrast logic must handle white-on-white**: B&W platforms need explicit check in `text_color_for_background()` to return black text for white backgrounds (otherwise invisible)
- **Confetti animation can safely skip B&W**: Colorful particles pointless on B&W displays; addition of `#if IS_BW_PLATFORM return;` early exit saves CPU cycles

