## Sessions

### Session: Phase 4 - B&W Platform Support (April 3, 2026)
**Objective**: Implement proper rendering for Pebble 2 and Pebble 2 Duo (black and white displays).

**Problem Discovered**: 
- Pebble 2 (diorite) and Pebble 2 Duo (flint) showed blank/white screens despite basalt showing full color UI
- Root cause: diorite/flint have PBL_COLOR defined but hardware can't render color properly, creating invisible backgrounds on white cards

**Implementation**:
1. Added `IS_BW_PLATFORM` macro to detect aplite, diorite, and flint
2. Modified `player_get_color()` to return white for B&W platforms only
3. Fixed `text_color_for_background()` to return black text for white backgrounds
4. Initially added numbered badges (1–4) in top-right to distinguish players on B&W
5. Refined design by removing redundant number badges (player names P1/P2/P3/P4 sufficient)
6. Disabled confetti animation on B&W platforms

**Results**:
- ✅ All 7 platforms now compile and render correctly
- ✅ B&W platforms (aplite, diorite, flint) show white cards with readable text and borders
- ✅ Color platforms (basalt, chalk, emery, gabbro) preserve full 4-color UI
- ✅ UI layout identical across platform types (consistent player names, scores, layout)
- ✅ Discovered and fixed text contrast bug (white-on-white invisible text)

**Key Learnings**:
- PBL_COLOR insufficient for platform detection on Pebble 2/2 Duo
- Player names alone are adequate distinction; avoid redundant numeric badges
- B&W support requires careful text contrast consideration
- Can safely optimize animations (skip confetti) on limited platforms

**Resolved Issues**: R-007

